nd fellow citizens think of him? In Pericles: A Sourcebook and Reader, Stephen V. Tracy visits the fifth century B.C. to find out. Tracy compiles and translates the scattered, elusive primary sources relating to Pericles. He brings Athens's political atmosphere to life with archaeological evidence and the accounts of those close to Pericles, including Thucydides, Aristophanes, Herodotus, Protagoras, Sophocles, Lysias, Xenophon, Plato, and Plutarch. Readers will discover Pericles as a formidable politician, a persuasive and inspiring orator, and a man full of human contradictions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aOratorszGreecezAthensvBiography. 0aStatesmenzGreecezAthensvBiography. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aage of pericles.  aancient greece.  aancient greek history.  aarcheology.  aaristophanes.  aathenian society.  aathens.  adelian league.  ademigod.  ademocracy.  afirst citizen of athens.  agolden age of greece.  agovernment and governing.  agreece.  agreek general.  agreek orator.  agreek statesman.  aherodotus.  alysias.  aparthenon.  apeloponnesian war.  apericles.  apersian war.  aplato.  aplutarch.  apolitical.  apolitics.  aprotagoras.  asophocles.  athucydides.  awarfare.  axenophon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025604040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094362940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943629423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943629/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY